Short SummaryHi! I'm Edoardo and about 4 years ago I have founded the International Security Observer - ISO (http://securityobserver.org/), a web-magazine for young professionals in foreign affairs. Since then, ISO has sought to foster the next generation of security experts by encouraging discussion on strategic issues among peers. Our next step is to establish ISO as a non-profit organization, providing training activities to recent graduates and young professionals wanting to build a career in the security sector. Through this crowdfunding campaign, you will help us to:  

Setting up our first office in Brussels. Depending on the budget, we plan on extending our activities in Washington DC and, if possible, elsewhere;
Carrying out training activities to help young professionals in the early stage of their careers acquiring practical skills;
Help students and young professionals finding paid internships and job opportunities;
Sustaining our website and editorial activities;

   What We Need & What You Get We are seeking to raise at least 300.000 €.
This money will be used for:



Rent an office in Brussels (and possibly in Washington DC) = 80/ 100.000 € / year

Employ 3 full time staff employees = 100.000 € / year 
Organize training activities on practical skills (e.g. Trend / Scenario analysis, Open Source Intelligence, Big Data and predictive analytics, etc.) = 80.000 € / year
Fund for post-training paid internships in public and private organizations = 20-30.000 € / year
   The Impact Our mission is to fill the gap between the academic and the professional world. Through our training activities we aim at shortening the time of unemployment of young professionals with an educational background in social science (politics, economy, law, etc.).
We have already build a worldwide network of public and private organizations willing to provide their expertise in coaching, as well as in hosting qualified interns.   
    Risks & Challenges The main challenges will be:


To reach out students and young professionals willing to participate to our training activities;
Finding senior experts in their field willing to coach the younger generation;

We are planning to overcome these issues by creating strategic partnerships with universities and public and private institutions. We are already in discussion with 3 Universities, consulting companies and non-profit organizations willing to provide experts and internship opportunities.     Other Ways You Can Help If you are not in the position to contribute, help us by spreading the word around! Like our Facebook page and Twitter and share our content to create awareness!
